      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hydration is good for overall health, but drinking more water won't \"flush out\" lithium; it's a chemical in your system that needs careful management. If your doctor said you need to adjust, they are likely referring to a dosage change, not just waiting it out. Since you are experiencing these symptoms, try taking a small, consistent dose of an over-the-counter anti-nausea aid with a meal, but seriously, call your doctor's office and explain the severity of your symptoms to see if they can offer a quick advice line call.",
