    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You absolutely must *not* take an extra dose of lithium without medical guidance; increasing the dosage on your own is a dangerous and potentially toxic move. Lithium has a very narrow therapeutic window, meaning too much can cause serious problems, not just \"level things out.\" Instead of risking an overdose, try a very mild, safe anti-spasmodic supplement with food, and focus on keeping your electrolyte balance stable with balanced meals.",
